KATSINA – The new Commissioner of Police in Katsina state, CP Idrisu Dauda Dabban has expressed the readiness of the command to synergize with other security agencies in the fight against the menace of banditry and other criminal elements bedevilling the state. Dabban gave the assurance when he paid a courtesy visit on the Secretary to the Government of the State, SGS, Alhaji Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa in his office. “I am aware of the level of insecurity in the state, I was adequately briefed by my predecessor on the state government’s commitment to bring an end to the crisis”. Police Foil Attack, Recover Arms, Ammunition In Kaduna Police Arrest 11 Nigerians For Cyber Fraud In Ghana “I will do my utmost best, under my leadership with other security agencies to curtail the activities of the terrorists, especially in the Frontline Local Government Areas in the state”, he assured. He, therefore, solicited for the continued support of the state government to enable him to discharge the onerous task ahead. Alhaji Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa, the Secretary to the Government of the state, SGS, in his response, assured the new CP of the state government’s commitment to provide the necessary logistics support to the security agencies to ensure that peace prevails in the state. While commending the efforts made in tackling the lingering menace in the state, the SGS charged them to do more, as many of the rural areas were under severe threat of the terrorists.